President Donald Trump visited Japan as part of his trip to Asia. During his visit, he met with American and Japanese military service members, had bilateral meetings with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe, met with the Emperor and Empress of Japan, engaged with business leaders, and met with the families of Japanese citizens abducted by North Korea. The visit aimed to strengthen the United States-Japan Alliance, increase pressure on North Korea, enhance economic engagement, and align strategic priorities in the Indo-Pacific region. Trump thanked Abe for his efforts in pressuring North Korea and emphasized the need to address the trade deficit between the two countries. He also expressed support for Japan's permanent membership on a reformed UN Security Council.